  "summary": "mailconfirmer ships an install-time PowerShell-spawning hook",
  "details": "The package contains an install-hook.js that requires child_process and invokes spawn('powershell',...) at install time. A package named 'mailconfirmer' has no legitimate reason to spawn a PowerShell subprocess from a lifecycle script; this is the canonical shape of an install-time dropper or command-execution stage running automatically when a developer or build system runs `npm install`. Combined with the package name's mail/confirmation lure (typical for credential-themed bait), the install hook executes attacker-chosen logic on the installer's machine without consent.",
